  <!-- FAQ for extra SEO & rich snippets -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions About Nepali Months</h2>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.2rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem;">How many months are in the Nepali calendar?</h3>
      <p>There are 12 standard months in Bikram Sambat, plus an occasional extra month (Adhik Maas) every 2–3 years.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.2rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem;">Which Nepali month is Dashain in?</h3>
      <p>Dashain falls in <strong>Ashwin</strong> (also called Ashoj) – typically from late Ashwin to early Kartik.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.2rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem;">What is the Nepali month for Tihar?</h3>
      <p>Tihar (Deepawali) is celebrated in <strong>Kartik</strong>, the seventh month of the BS calendar.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem;">What is the first Nepali month?</h3>
      <p>Baishakh is the first month of Bikram Sambat. The Nepali New Year starts on Baishakh 1.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

